│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The logic for `isGather()` at line 11061 seems relevant. It calls `processBuildVector`, which is where the crash happens. The condition `E->isGather()` is true for the reduction,       │
│ because the vectorizer treats it as a gather of scalars.                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Inside the `if (E->isGather())` block, there are some checks. If it's not all constants and not an `InsertElementInst`, it calls `processBuildVector`. This is the path taken for the    │
│ reproducer.                                                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The `processBuildVector` function is a template that uses a `ShuffleCostEstimator`. The estimator's `finalize` method is where the assertion fails. This means the information passed to │
│ `processBuildVector` is not quite right.                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The `zext from i1` is the root of the problem. The vectorizer should recognize this as a special case, a horizontal reduction that produces a single scalar.                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will add a check for `zext from i1` inside the `isGather()` block. If the main op of the tree entry is a `zext from i1`, I will manually calculate the cost of a shuffle that extracts │
│ the first element and returns. This avoids calling `processBuildVector` with incorrect parameters.                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The main op is `E->getMainOp()`. The vector length is `VL.size()`.                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   if (E->isGather()) {                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<ZExtInst>(E->getMainOp())) {                                                                                                                                  │
│       if (I->getOperand(0)->getType()->isIntegerTy(1)) {                                                                                                                                 │
│         // Special handling for zext from i1. This is a horizontal reduction.                                                                                                            │
│         SmallVector<int, 16> PermMask(VL.size(), PoisonMaskElem);                                                                                                                        │
│         PermMask[0] = 0;                                                                                                                                                                 │
│         auto Cost = TTI->getShuffleCost(TargetTransformInfo::SK_PermuteSingleSrc,                                                                                                        │
│                                        VectorType::get(I->getType(), VL.size()),                                                                                                         │
